{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Pastry","content":["Place flour, butter and salt in mixing bowl then pulse <b>Turbo\/1 sec\/4 times<b> until fine crumbs form.","Add egg yolk and water then knead <b>1 min\/<b>, adding another 1 Tbsp water if necessary to help mixture come together. Tip out onto a floured surface and roll out thinly. Use a pastry cutter to cut out discs large enough to line 6 loose-based tartlet tins (Ø 10 cm). Prick bases with a fork then chill for 20 minutes. Meanwhile, preheat oven to 200°C.","Line chilled tart cases with baking paper and fill with baking beans then blind bake for 10 minutes (200°C). Remove baking beans and paper then bake for a further 5-10 minutes (200°C) until golden. Set aside in tins to cool."]},{"title":"Filling","content":["Place 20 g butter, garlic, spring onions, green pepper and celery in mixing bowl then chop <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then sauté <b>5 min\/100°C\/speed <b>.","Add crayfish and heat <b>2 min\/100°C\/\/speed <b>. Transfer to a bowl and keep warm.","Place remaining 20 g butter in mixing bowl and melt <b>1 min 30 sec\/100°C\/speed 1<b>.","Avoiding blades, add flour and cook <b>3 min\/100°C\/speed 0.5<b>.","Add milk, Cajun spice mix, salt and pepper then cook <b>6 min\/90°C\/speed 4<b>.","Using a slotted spoon, add reserved crayfish mixture and 1-2 Tbsp of their juices (see tip) then stir <b>20 sec\/\/speed 0.5<b>. Spoon into cooked tart cases, garnish with parsley (if using) and serve immediately."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Pastry","content":["175 g plain flour, plus extra for dusting","90 g unsalted butter, cold, diced","1 pinch fine sea salt","1 egg yolk, from medium egg","1 - 2 Tbsp water"]},{"title":"Filling","content":["40 g unsalted butter, diced","1 garlic clove","6 spring onions, cut in pieces (3 cm)","½ green pepper, quartered","1 celery stalk, quartered","200 g crayfish tails, cooked","20 g plain flour","220 g whole milk","¼ tsp Cajun spice mix","¼ tsp fine sea salt","1 pinch ground black pepper","fresh parsley leaves, roughly chopped, for garnishing (optional)"]}],"id":"r209279","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-_7z4nbrSDdQ\/XZQv4b23-7I\/AAAAAAAAcgo\/2vvHi6Dklv0m6sEbAKXM3sa2JJO9JdRRgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_OY9fzsj3HfJGBIPd.png","title":"Crayfish Pies","publishedAt":"2019-02-18T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"11 g","fat":"21 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"27 g","calories":"1434 kJ \/ 344 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking paper, baking beans, rolling pin, loose-based tartlet tins (Ø 10 cm), pastry cutter, slotted spoon, oven, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["In Louisiana, these tarts are known as Crawfish Pies, which are mentioned in the famous Hank Williams song \"Jambalaya (On the Bayou)\".","When adding cooking juices in <b>step 9,<b> try to keep the sauce quite a thick consistency."],"basicInfo":["medium","20m","1h 15m","6 portions"]}